                    "description": "Provision  of analysis, evaluation, training and advisory services to international, governmental and non-governmental organizations. \n\nPrimary areas of expertise are post-conflict development and governance, demilitarization and peace-building. \n\nMain assignments included: \n-  Research and drafting for UNDP guide on community-based reintegration (CBR) support (2020/21);\n-  Assisting the EU in drafting of its new strategic Concept for support to DDR activities (2020/21);\n-  Member of the team drafting proposed EU action in support of the implementation of the August 2019 Peace Accord in Mozambique (DDR and reconciliation) (2019);\n-  Assisting UN agencies in revising the guidance on reintegration support in the UN Integrated DDR Standards (IDDRS) (2019);\n-  Senior Advisor at BICC, Bonn (2018);\n-  Team leader of Rehabilitation Support Team in Somalia (2015/16);\n-  Researcher and lead author of World Bank/UNHCR study on Forced Displacement in the Great Lakes Region (Africa) (2014);\n-  Drafting the African Union (AU) Operational Guidelines on National Frameworks for Disarmament, Demobilization and Reintegration (DDR) (2013/14);\n-  Principal Capacity Building Mentor of the South Sudan National DDR Commission (2013);\n-  Preparing the business plan on Community Security and Justice for a large social enterprise (2012);\n-  Leading a 'lessons learned' process within the UN System in Nepal (2012); \n-  Tutor of Internet-based UN course on the UN Integrated Disarmament, Demobilization and Reintegration Standards (IDDRS) (2012);\n-  Facilitation and strategic/technical advice on rehabilitation issues in Nepal (2011/12); \n-  Advisor to the Government of South Sudan regarding its new Disarmament, Demobilization and Reintegration (DDR) policy and strategy (2011); and\n-  Team leader for the Southern Sudan component of the independent Review of the Sudan Disarmament, Demobilization and Reintegration (DDR) Programme (2010).",
